1
00:00:14,360 --> 00:00:17,440
♪In the airport lounge
at the break of day♪

2
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:22,240
♪A page of dust beneath my fingers♪

3
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:25,160
♪Filled with stories♪

4
00:00:25,160 --> 00:00:28,280
♪That others never got to tell♪

5
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,960
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

6
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:35,600
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

7
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:37,160
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

8
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:40,040
♪The world is split an inch wider♪

9
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:42,600
♪Raise your eyes, face the light♪

10
00:00:42,760 --> 00:00:45,080
♪See the truth, and see the fright♪

11
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:46,800
♪Guard the crack within this door♪

12
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:52,600
♪Keep the way back home
always burning bright♪

13
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:57,040
♪The camera pans
across the boarding crowd♪

14
00:00:57,080 --> 00:00:59,200
♪Some wear a smile,
some have their eyes adrift♪

15
00:00:59,280 --> 00:01:01,440
♪A red suitcase♪

16
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:05,360
♪Tied with faded pasts
and broken prayers♪

17
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:09,400
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

18
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:12,080
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

19
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:13,960
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

20
00:01:14,040 --> 00:01:17,400
♪It's the heartbeat
echoing the call of law♪

21
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:30,000
[Gimlet Eyes]

22
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:32,960
[Episode 19]

23
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:39,460
Bye. Take care.

24
00:01:39,480 --> 00:01:40,380
- Bye, take care. - Bye.

25
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:41,540
Hope to see you on board again.

26
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:42,490
Bye.

27
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:43,260
Bye.

28
00:01:43,430 --> 00:01:44,330
Hope to fly with you again soon.

29
00:01:44,350 --> 00:01:45,020
Bye. Take care.

30
00:01:45,040 --> 00:01:46,260
Hope to see you on board again.

31
00:01:46,430 --> 00:01:47,690
Goodbye. Have a nice day.

32
00:01:49,120 --> 00:01:50,290
Goodbye. Have a nice day.

33
00:01:50,310 --> 00:01:50,770
Bye.

34
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:51,770
Bye.

35
00:01:51,790 --> 00:01:52,260
Bye.

36
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:53,260
Bye. Take care.

37
00:01:54,590 --> 00:01:55,900
- Take care. - Take care.

38
00:02:02,120 --> 00:02:03,020
- Bye. - Bye.

39
00:02:03,040 --> 00:02:04,020
Bye. Good work today.

40
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:04,770
Bye, Tao.

41
00:02:04,790 --> 00:02:05,770
Good work. Bye.

42
00:02:05,790 --> 00:02:07,180
We'll get going then. Bye.

43
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:07,820
Bye.

44
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:15,100
Hurry, get the case out.

45
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:27,060
Stop looking.

46
00:02:27,080 --> 00:02:28,780
Cleaning staff won't be here that soon.

47
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:35,730
Let's split up.

48
00:02:35,750 --> 00:02:37,100
Meet in the restroom.

49
00:02:44,310 --> 00:02:45,260
Tao.

50
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:47,940
I'm so sorry, I…

51
00:02:48,080 --> 00:02:49,010
I can't.

52
00:02:49,360 --> 00:02:51,170
I really can't.

53
00:02:57,400 --> 00:02:58,170
Shen Taotao,

54
00:02:58,520 --> 00:03:00,220
you're suspected of
smuggling ivory products.

55
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:01,540
Please come with us.

56
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:04,780
It's my fault.

57
00:03:05,360 --> 00:03:06,540
All my fault.

58
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:15,890
Tao,

59
00:03:15,910 --> 00:03:17,010
my boyfriend's here to pick me up.

60
00:03:17,030 --> 00:03:18,410
Let us give you a ride.

61
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:19,940
Don't wait for the shuttle.

62
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:20,850
Thanks,

63
00:03:20,870 --> 00:03:22,410
but I don't wanna
crash your romantic time.

64
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:24,850
Come on, we're friends.

65
00:03:25,310 --> 00:03:26,540
- Zihan, get in. - Bye.

66
00:03:26,910 --> 00:03:27,780
See you then.

67
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:28,610
Off you go.

68
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:29,890
- Bye. - See you.

69
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:30,610
Coming.

70
00:03:51,430 --> 00:03:52,610
Ms. Sa, you're here!

71
00:03:56,470 --> 00:03:57,820
This way, Ms. Sa.

72
00:04:05,030 --> 00:04:05,730
Ms. Sa, welcome.

73
00:04:06,960 --> 00:04:08,540
Another new car?

74
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:09,500
Just got it.

75
00:04:10,030 --> 00:04:11,010
Might rain later.

76
00:04:11,030 --> 00:04:12,170
I'll park it in the basement for you.

77
00:04:12,870 --> 00:04:13,290
Thanks.

78
00:04:59,270 --> 00:05:00,020
Zihan.

79
00:05:01,270 --> 00:05:02,460
Tao!

80
00:05:02,680 --> 00:05:04,220
Come on, I'll take you to the airport.

81
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:04,900
See you then.

82
00:05:05,270 --> 00:05:05,610
Okay,

83
00:05:05,630 --> 00:05:06,460
bye!

84
00:05:11,510 --> 00:05:12,900
Nice one, Tao.

85
00:05:13,360 --> 00:05:15,370
Showing up in a luxury car now?

86
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:17,580
Better to rely on yourself
than on anyone else.

87
00:05:18,190 --> 00:05:18,660
True.

88
00:06:31,120 --> 00:06:31,980
What else did you find?

89
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:32,580
Keep going.

90
00:06:33,070 --> 00:06:33,460
Right,

91
00:06:34,870 --> 00:06:35,810
I found out

92
00:06:35,920 --> 00:06:36,780
Sa Ziyi

93
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:38,900
used to have four capable men,

94
00:06:39,430 --> 00:06:40,700
each in charge of different channels.

95
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:41,900
But they all got arrested later.

96
00:06:42,430 --> 00:06:43,700
As for Long Shuo,

97
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:45,020
he was Sa Ziyi's lover.

98
00:06:46,510 --> 00:06:48,850
He didn't handle any real business.

99
00:06:49,480 --> 00:06:50,660
More like

100
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:53,370
a bodyguard and advisor.

101
00:06:55,950 --> 00:06:56,540
That's it?

102
00:06:57,270 --> 00:06:57,980
No, there's more.

103
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:01,100
I asked a prison buddy to check for me.

104
00:07:01,310 --> 00:07:02,700
Got some big news.

105
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:04,370
Sa Ziyi had

106
00:07:04,390 --> 00:07:07,580
a secret mule hound working for her.

107
00:07:08,070 --> 00:07:08,900
Mule hound?

108
00:07:09,270 --> 00:07:09,660
Yeah.

109
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:10,810
That's what they called him.

110
00:07:12,190 --> 00:07:13,580
My buddy said

111
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:14,700
only Sa Ziyi

112
00:07:14,720 --> 00:07:16,490
has ever seen this mule hound.

113
00:07:16,750 --> 00:07:17,540
Very mysterious.

114
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:19,850
His only job was finding mules.

115
00:07:20,270 --> 00:07:21,660
Had nothing to do with other operations.

116
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:23,780
No idea if he

117
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:25,020
got arrested or not.

118
00:07:25,510 --> 00:07:26,780
Only responsible for finding mules?

119
00:07:26,830 --> 00:07:27,340
Yes.

120
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:31,170
Sounds a lot like Mr. E.

121
00:07:31,170 --> 00:07:34,640
[Mr. E]

122
00:07:35,630 --> 00:07:37,050
Mr. E, it's me.

123
00:07:37,510 --> 00:07:38,170
I know.

124
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,220
Got the photos.

125
00:07:40,390 --> 00:07:41,580
Are they all mules?

126
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:43,850
All potential mules.

127
00:07:44,630 --> 00:07:45,900
[Shen Taotao, stewardess. Needs money.]
On each photo's back,

128
00:07:46,390 --> 00:07:47,540
[Shen Taotao, stewardess. Needs money.]
I noted their current situation

129
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:49,730
[Believes in love, scorns gold-diggers.]
and weaknesses briefly.

130
00:07:49,730 --> 00:07:50,440
[Shen Taotao, stewardess. Needs money.
Believes in love, scorns gold-diggers.]

131
00:07:50,630 --> 00:07:52,220
When you need mules,

132
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:53,140
go find them.

133
00:07:53,630 --> 00:07:55,170
You know what to say, right?

134
00:07:55,430 --> 00:07:56,020
Yeah,

135
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:57,780
I know what to say.

136
00:07:58,480 --> 00:07:59,020
Remember,

137
00:07:59,750 --> 00:08:00,810
give them

138
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:02,140
whatever they're lacking.

139
00:08:03,390 --> 00:08:04,410
What else could they need?

140
00:08:04,430 --> 00:08:05,340
Money, obviously.

141
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:07,700
You don't understand people at all.

142
00:08:08,510 --> 00:08:10,700
Everyone has different needs.

143
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:13,410
Some need money,

144
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:15,460
others crave love,

145
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:17,930
and some just want to be recognized.

146
00:08:18,830 --> 00:08:21,170
Don't think one approach

147
00:08:21,190 --> 00:08:22,540
works for everyone.

148
00:08:23,510 --> 00:08:24,540
Understood, Mr. E.

149
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:27,250
Li,

150
00:08:29,160 --> 00:08:31,370
could Mr. E be the mule hound?

151
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:34,180
Long Shuo, her personal bodyguard,

152
00:08:34,840 --> 00:08:36,650
could he have seen him?

153
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:38,130
Very likely.

154
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:39,980
That's why I want you

155
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:41,460
to find Long Shuo right now!

156
00:08:44,030 --> 00:08:45,300
If Mr. E

157
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:47,220
is the mule hound,

158
00:08:48,550 --> 00:08:50,530
he's a backstabbing traitor,

159
00:08:51,150 --> 00:08:52,460
an old dog you can never tame.

160
00:08:54,360 --> 00:08:55,130
Li,

161
00:08:55,790 --> 00:08:56,890
none of us

162
00:08:57,080 --> 00:08:58,650
has ever seen this old dog.

163
00:08:59,270 --> 00:09:00,010
Doesn't matter.

164
00:09:00,670 --> 00:09:02,010
I know how to lure him out.

165
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:03,250
How?

166
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:04,610
Ever raised a dog?

167
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:05,770
No.

168
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:07,370
Every dog

169
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:09,130
has a favorite toy.

170
00:09:09,550 --> 00:09:11,300
Take it away,

171
00:09:11,750 --> 00:09:12,820
and it'll bark at you.

172
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:29,010
Hello?

173
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:30,250
Mr. E,

174
00:09:30,790 --> 00:09:31,980
I've got bad news.

175
00:09:32,670 --> 00:09:33,940
Shen Taotao got caught.

176
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:34,770
What?

177
00:09:35,720 --> 00:09:37,300
Shen Taotao got caught?

178
00:09:38,510 --> 00:09:39,370
Yeah.

179
00:09:40,150 --> 00:09:41,700
Never saw it coming.

180
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:42,770
I told you not to let her

181
00:09:42,790 --> 00:09:44,490
run any more shipments!

182
00:09:44,510 --> 00:09:45,300
What happened?

183
00:09:45,510 --> 00:09:47,890
Yes, I remember you told me that.

184
00:09:48,080 --> 00:09:50,180
I passed your order down right away.

185
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:53,060
But she insisted on one last run.

186
00:09:53,390 --> 00:09:54,580
And then

187
00:09:54,790 --> 00:09:56,300
this happened.

188
00:09:56,630 --> 00:09:57,220
Well,

189
00:09:57,480 --> 00:09:58,580
Mr. E…

190
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:06,180
Forget about her.

191
00:10:07,510 --> 00:10:09,100
Everyone has their fate,

192
00:10:10,120 --> 00:10:11,300
right, Du Li?

193
00:10:12,550 --> 00:10:13,130
Yes,

194
00:10:13,150 --> 00:10:13,580
exactly.

195
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:15,340
By the way,

196
00:10:15,480 --> 00:10:15,980
I have

197
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:17,700
something else to tell you.

198
00:10:18,440 --> 00:10:18,890
Go on.

199
00:10:19,270 --> 00:10:22,130
I've found some new mules lately.

200
00:10:22,240 --> 00:10:23,420
Pretty good ones.

201
00:10:23,550 --> 00:10:24,980
I'm planning to use them.

202
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:26,370
You can hold off

203
00:10:26,390 --> 00:10:28,610
on finding mules for a while.

204
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:31,460
I'll let you know if I need more.

205
00:10:38,270 --> 00:10:39,060
Du Li,

206
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:42,980
have you forgotten our rules?

207
00:10:43,790 --> 00:10:44,730
Mr. E,

208
00:10:45,270 --> 00:10:47,250
times have changed.

209
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:49,340
Maybe

210
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:50,940
our relationship

211
00:10:50,960 --> 00:10:52,340
should change too.

212
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:54,770
Fine.

213
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:56,180
How?

214
00:10:58,840 --> 00:11:00,100
Give me some time to think.

215
00:11:00,510 --> 00:11:01,850
Once I've decided,

216
00:11:02,390 --> 00:11:03,730
we can meet in person.

217
00:11:09,390 --> 00:11:10,130
Meet in person?

218
00:11:10,320 --> 00:11:11,580
Yeah, in person.

219
00:11:11,790 --> 00:11:13,460
It's been so long,

220
00:11:13,750 --> 00:11:15,100
and we've never met.

221
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:17,250
Doesn't feel right, huh?

222
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:19,010
I think a face-to-face meeting

223
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:20,820
would help

224
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:22,610
build more trust between us.

225
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:28,820
Alright.

226
00:11:30,080 --> 00:11:31,580
Go think it over carefully.

227
00:11:32,240 --> 00:11:34,340
Then we'll arrange a meeting.

228
00:12:12,880 --> 00:12:16,880
[Five Years Ago
2019]

229
00:12:26,080 --> 00:12:26,850
Xiang,

230
00:12:27,720 --> 00:12:28,420
- I'm here. - Sa.

231
00:12:29,910 --> 00:12:30,700
Perfect timing.

232
00:12:30,790 --> 00:12:31,890
I just

233
00:12:31,910 --> 00:12:33,610
brewed some Yiwu black tea.

234
00:12:34,270 --> 00:12:34,850
Try it.

235
00:12:36,750 --> 00:12:37,850
You know what?

236
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:39,650
You'd rather spend a fortune

237
00:12:39,670 --> 00:12:41,130
on an old tea garden

238
00:12:41,270 --> 00:12:43,460
than fix this place up.

239
00:12:44,360 --> 00:12:45,460
After all these years,

240
00:12:46,510 --> 00:12:48,460
nothing's changed.

241
00:12:50,630 --> 00:12:51,700
It's just an office.

242
00:12:51,750 --> 00:12:52,890
As long as it works.

243
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:55,300
Don't want to be too flashy.

244
00:12:56,440 --> 00:12:57,580
What do you want to see me about?

245
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:02,580
Listen,

246
00:13:03,870 --> 00:13:04,820
we're changing,

247
00:13:05,510 --> 00:13:07,060
the market's changing too.

248
00:13:08,550 --> 00:13:09,580
So,

249
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:11,530
shouldn't we maybe

250
00:13:11,750 --> 00:13:13,610
stop sticking to the old rules?

251
00:13:19,720 --> 00:13:20,820
You want to deal drugs?

252
00:13:22,910 --> 00:13:23,460
Yes.

253
00:13:23,910 --> 00:13:24,940
Airport too.

254
00:13:25,960 --> 00:13:26,820
If we do this,

255
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:27,890
we go big.

256
00:13:28,480 --> 00:13:29,300
The thing is,

257
00:13:29,320 --> 00:13:30,530
drugs are different.

258
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:32,890
Once you touch them,

259
00:13:33,150 --> 00:13:34,180
people die.

260
00:13:34,960 --> 00:13:36,980
And Customs is cracking down hard.

261
00:13:37,790 --> 00:13:39,130
If they find out,

262
00:13:39,150 --> 00:13:40,650
they'll hunt us down

263
00:13:40,670 --> 00:13:41,770
and dig everything up.

264
00:13:42,270 --> 00:13:43,340
I know.

265
00:13:43,910 --> 00:13:46,180
But high reward means high risk, right?

266
00:13:47,120 --> 00:13:48,730
I'll be straight with you.

267
00:13:49,080 --> 00:13:50,100
I'm already

268
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:52,250
moving on this.

269
00:13:55,270 --> 00:13:56,220
So,

270
00:13:56,790 --> 00:13:58,220
you just focus on

271
00:13:58,320 --> 00:13:59,490
finding me the mules.

272
00:14:02,030 --> 00:14:02,820
Fine.

273
00:14:23,960 --> 00:14:25,060
Let me talk business.

274
00:14:25,910 --> 00:14:27,180
That Lari,

275
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:28,370
when's he coming back?

276
00:14:29,270 --> 00:14:30,420
It's all set.

277
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:31,850
Flight on the seventh.

278
00:14:32,150 --> 00:14:33,100
He'll go straight

279
00:14:33,480 --> 00:14:34,890
to the drop after landing.

280
00:14:35,280 --> 00:14:36,120
[Lari, May 7th Long Shuo]

281
00:14:36,120 --> 00:14:38,130
[Lari, May 7th Long Shuo]
This is our first drug run.

282
00:14:39,030 --> 00:14:40,340
We spent so much on it.

283
00:14:40,480 --> 00:14:41,770
It has to go right.

284
00:14:43,120 --> 00:14:43,980
Relax.

285
00:14:44,750 --> 00:14:46,010
I've arranged other mules.

286
00:14:46,960 --> 00:14:48,580
I'll have them carry small loads first,

287
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:49,980
as cannon fodder.

288
00:14:51,270 --> 00:14:52,180
After all,

289
00:14:52,440 --> 00:14:54,530
we can't rely on
that hound forever, right?

290
00:15:31,880 --> 00:15:36,480
[May 7th, Drugs]

291
00:15:40,390 --> 00:15:42,060
Ms. Sa, you sent for me?

292
00:15:42,080 --> 00:15:43,300
Any instructions?

293
00:15:45,270 --> 00:15:46,650
Can't say instructions.

294
00:15:47,390 --> 00:15:48,700
I'll be straight with you.

295
00:15:50,240 --> 00:15:51,010
I

296
00:15:51,790 --> 00:15:53,220
want you on my team.

297
00:15:54,120 --> 00:15:54,980
Work for you?

298
00:15:56,240 --> 00:15:57,850
I'm starting a new operation.

299
00:15:58,040 --> 00:15:58,940
Need people.

300
00:15:59,390 --> 00:16:00,220
I've

301
00:16:00,630 --> 00:16:02,370
had my eye on you for a while.

302
00:16:02,760 --> 00:16:04,650
You're short on men,

303
00:16:05,390 --> 00:16:06,340
but you're tough.

304
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:09,100
Come work for me.

305
00:16:09,510 --> 00:16:10,530
You won't regret it.

306
00:16:12,480 --> 00:16:14,010
Ms. Sa, you flatter me.

307
00:16:15,120 --> 00:16:17,100
We just move cheap goods.

308
00:16:17,520 --> 00:16:18,490
Making a living.

309
00:16:19,280 --> 00:16:20,300
I don't want any part

310
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:21,370
of your big business.

311
00:16:21,750 --> 00:16:22,580
What,

312
00:16:23,670 --> 00:16:24,650
you don't want to?

313
00:16:25,280 --> 00:16:26,530
You might not know.

314
00:16:27,040 --> 00:16:28,980
We came up from the streets.

315
00:16:29,760 --> 00:16:31,460
Always kept our heads down.

316
00:16:32,510 --> 00:16:35,060
Finally, we have
our own little business.

317
00:16:35,360 --> 00:16:36,940
It's not much yet,

318
00:16:37,360 --> 00:16:38,130
but

319
00:16:38,640 --> 00:16:40,580
we don't have to take orders
from anyone anymore.

320
00:16:40,870 --> 00:16:43,060
If you're talking partnership,

321
00:16:43,270 --> 00:16:44,340
I'm all for it.

322
00:16:45,360 --> 00:16:47,530
But working under you?

323
00:16:49,160 --> 00:16:49,940
I can't do that.

324
00:16:50,270 --> 00:16:51,890
So you're saying

325
00:16:52,670 --> 00:16:54,100
you want to be my equal?

326
00:16:55,750 --> 00:16:57,420
Not yet, not in strength.

327
00:16:57,790 --> 00:16:58,820
But in the future?

328
00:16:59,400 --> 00:17:00,460
Who knows?

329
00:17:00,760 --> 00:17:02,180
Ambitious.

330
00:17:02,870 --> 00:17:03,890
I wasn't wrong about you.

331
00:17:06,720 --> 00:17:07,620
But listen,

332
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:09,250
in the airport,

333
00:17:10,270 --> 00:17:11,700
with one word from me,

334
00:17:12,720 --> 00:17:13,980
you can't move a thing.

335
00:17:14,040 --> 00:17:15,660
I know you have men

336
00:17:15,720 --> 00:17:16,620
and connections.

337
00:17:17,350 --> 00:17:18,620
But honestly,

338
00:17:18,790 --> 00:17:20,090
I don't buy your words.

339
00:17:22,270 --> 00:17:23,900
Customs doesn't answer to you.

340
00:17:25,720 --> 00:17:26,490
I've got things to do.

341
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:28,010
Save the lecture.

342
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:29,900
Stay where you are.

343
00:17:31,270 --> 00:17:32,460
I don't remember saying you could leave.

344
00:17:35,350 --> 00:17:36,180
What do you want?

345
00:17:40,510 --> 00:17:41,730
Forgot to mention.

346
00:17:42,440 --> 00:17:43,530
I hold grudges.

347
00:17:44,070 --> 00:17:45,570
You'd better just kill me.

348
00:17:46,350 --> 00:17:48,220
Because if I recover from this,

349
00:17:48,350 --> 00:17:50,010
I won't show any mercy.

350
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:00,090
Find some people.

351
00:18:01,070 --> 00:18:02,660
Cut off all her routes.

352
00:18:04,680 --> 00:18:06,180
I don't buy this attitude.

353
00:18:07,480 --> 00:18:08,530
Just a little brat.

354
00:18:09,350 --> 00:18:09,940
Let it go.

355
00:18:10,720 --> 00:18:11,940
Let her rot on her own.

356
00:18:13,520 --> 00:18:14,290
Du Li.

357
00:18:16,760 --> 00:18:17,730
Interesting.

358
00:18:34,550 --> 00:18:35,810
You're Du Li, right?

359
00:18:36,830 --> 00:18:37,730
I can help you.

360
00:18:39,030 --> 00:18:39,900
How?

361
00:18:40,440 --> 00:18:42,250
I'm Sa Ziyi's rival.

362
00:18:42,720 --> 00:18:44,810
I know all her channels and resources.

363
00:18:45,240 --> 00:18:47,090
I can help you take over quickly.

364
00:18:49,960 --> 00:18:55,520
[Old Shipyard]

365
00:18:55,520 --> 00:18:56,250
Xiang,

366
00:18:58,270 --> 00:18:59,660
I really admire you.

367
00:19:00,440 --> 00:19:02,010
How do you stay so calm?

368
00:19:03,280 --> 00:19:04,570
It's not that I'm calm.

369
00:19:05,110 --> 00:19:06,180
Some things.

370
00:19:06,280 --> 00:19:07,330
There's no use rushing.

371
00:19:09,830 --> 00:19:11,570
Why is this happening to us?

372
00:19:12,200 --> 00:19:14,090
Passenger Inspection

373
00:19:14,750 --> 00:19:16,090
has caught us so many times.

374
00:19:16,310 --> 00:19:17,860
I told you before,

375
00:19:17,960 --> 00:19:20,050
airport passenger inspection is tight.

376
00:19:20,920 --> 00:19:23,700
You think you're clever
smuggling through there?

377
00:19:23,830 --> 00:19:25,810
You think they don't see that?

378
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:28,420
If it's not working,
just drop that route.

379
00:19:28,760 --> 00:19:29,330
No.

380
00:19:30,830 --> 00:19:32,330
I don't buy it.

381
00:19:33,760 --> 00:19:34,810
I'm doing one more run.

382
00:19:40,310 --> 00:19:41,530
It's about the mules, isn't it?

383
00:19:46,030 --> 00:19:46,730
Yes.

384
00:19:48,030 --> 00:19:48,940
This time,

385
00:19:49,790 --> 00:19:51,220
I need a lot of kids.

386
00:19:52,110 --> 00:19:53,290
Are you serious?

387
00:19:54,070 --> 00:19:54,810
Of course.

388
00:19:55,750 --> 00:19:56,460
No.

389
00:19:57,240 --> 00:19:59,140
This crosses my line.

390
00:19:59,440 --> 00:20:00,900
I never use kids.

391
00:20:02,350 --> 00:20:04,250
I'm not asking you to use kids.

392
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:06,420
I'm asking you to use their parents.

393
00:20:06,440 --> 00:20:07,620
That's still a no.

394
00:20:09,550 --> 00:20:11,810
You're playing the saint now?

395
00:20:12,310 --> 00:20:15,380
How many mules
have you dragged into this?

396
00:20:16,110 --> 00:20:17,980
I didn't drag them into anything.

397
00:20:18,510 --> 00:20:20,460
They chose this.

398
00:20:20,750 --> 00:20:21,900
Kids are different.

399
00:20:22,510 --> 00:20:24,620
They don't understand choice.

400
00:20:26,310 --> 00:20:27,290
Will you do it or not?

401
00:20:29,590 --> 00:20:30,090
No.

402
00:20:31,830 --> 00:20:32,380
Fine.

403
00:20:33,720 --> 00:20:34,730
If you won't,

404
00:20:35,480 --> 00:20:36,140
I will.

405
00:20:36,310 --> 00:20:37,660
From now on,

406
00:20:37,680 --> 00:20:38,770
you stay out of the mule business.

407
00:20:47,960 --> 00:20:53,920
[Old Shipyard]

408
00:21:03,640 --> 00:21:04,770
Have you made up your mind?

409
00:21:04,880 --> 00:21:05,660
I have.

410
00:21:06,510 --> 00:21:07,730
Sa Ziyi's turf…

411
00:21:08,030 --> 00:21:08,730
I want all of it.

412
00:21:08,920 --> 00:21:10,860
And I want all your resources, too.

413
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:12,330
Okay.

414
00:21:12,350 --> 00:21:12,940
Wait.

415
00:21:14,200 --> 00:21:16,050
I can't just keep calling you 'hey'.

416
00:21:16,270 --> 00:21:17,770
What should I call you?

417
00:21:19,030 --> 00:21:20,860
Just call me Mr. E.

418
00:21:49,960 --> 00:21:50,900
Mr. E?

419
00:21:51,200 --> 00:21:51,860
That's me.

420
00:21:52,590 --> 00:21:53,620
Are you in Binhai?

421
00:21:53,880 --> 00:21:54,660
Yes.

422
00:21:55,510 --> 00:21:57,050
Do you have Sa Ziyi's number?

423
00:21:57,880 --> 00:21:58,980
I do. Why?

424
00:22:01,160 --> 00:22:02,940
Ask her to meet you now.

425
00:22:03,830 --> 00:22:06,180
Why would she want to see me now?

426
00:22:06,680 --> 00:22:07,900
Just tell her

427
00:22:07,920 --> 00:22:09,490
you know about those dolls.

428
00:22:09,510 --> 00:22:10,900
She'll definitely come.

429
00:22:11,480 --> 00:22:12,180
Dolls?

430
00:22:12,200 --> 00:22:13,050
What dolls?

431
00:22:14,830 --> 00:22:16,900
She's lost a few deals
to Customs lately.

432
00:22:16,920 --> 00:22:18,700
Each time, someone used dolls

433
00:22:18,720 --> 00:22:20,460
to tip them off.

434
00:22:22,200 --> 00:22:23,290
How do you know that?

435
00:22:23,960 --> 00:22:25,050
Don't tell me

436
00:22:25,720 --> 00:22:26,770
you're with Customs?

437
00:22:27,590 --> 00:22:29,420
I know a lot of things.

438
00:22:29,960 --> 00:22:31,900
And you don't need to guess who I am.

439
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:34,900
Today is your best chance.

440
00:22:35,440 --> 00:22:36,810
But what do I say to her?

441
00:22:41,070 --> 00:22:42,010
Talk to her

442
00:22:42,030 --> 00:22:44,050
woman to woman.

443
00:22:44,790 --> 00:22:45,420
Remember.

444
00:22:46,440 --> 00:22:47,700
Seventy percent truth,

445
00:22:47,720 --> 00:22:49,330
thirty percent lies,

446
00:22:49,550 --> 00:22:51,420
and she'll believe your story.

447
00:22:52,550 --> 00:22:53,570
When you go,

448
00:22:53,590 --> 00:22:55,250
bring a good bottle.

449
00:22:55,750 --> 00:22:57,140
The kind that gets her drunk

450
00:22:57,680 --> 00:22:58,860
and makes sure she never wakes up.

451
00:23:02,350 --> 00:23:03,730
You want me to…

452
00:23:04,960 --> 00:23:06,570
You know what kind of person

453
00:23:06,590 --> 00:23:07,620
Sa Ziyi is.

454
00:23:08,550 --> 00:23:10,140
If you let her get away,

455
00:23:10,550 --> 00:23:11,330
sooner or later,

456
00:23:11,350 --> 00:23:12,980
she'll come back to Binhai.

457
00:23:13,590 --> 00:23:14,940
When that happens,

458
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:16,420
do you think you can beat her?

459
00:23:18,790 --> 00:23:19,620
But…

460
00:23:19,720 --> 00:23:20,810
No buts.

461
00:23:21,270 --> 00:23:22,380
If you don't do it,

462
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:24,530
our deal is off.

463
00:23:29,830 --> 00:23:30,380
Fine.

464
00:23:30,480 --> 00:23:31,180
I'll do it.

465
00:24:41,790 --> 00:24:43,490
Why'd you pick a place like this?

466
00:26:11,070 --> 00:26:11,700
Hello?

467
00:26:12,440 --> 00:26:13,220
It's me.

468
00:26:13,480 --> 00:26:14,330
Mr. E.

469
00:26:14,720 --> 00:26:15,660
Mr. E?

470
00:26:15,720 --> 00:26:16,180
You…

471
00:26:16,200 --> 00:26:17,770
This is my real voice.

472
00:26:18,550 --> 00:26:20,050
I'm not worried anymore

473
00:26:20,070 --> 00:26:22,090
about you letting Sa Ziyi hear my voice.

474
00:26:22,110 --> 00:26:23,220
Don't worry. She…

475
00:26:23,240 --> 00:26:24,420
didn't recognize it.

476
00:26:24,640 --> 00:26:25,620
Don't be nervous.

477
00:26:25,750 --> 00:26:27,530
I'd have done the same thing.

478
00:26:28,070 --> 00:26:29,940
Who could feel at ease

479
00:26:29,960 --> 00:26:31,810
with an unseen ghost at their side?

480
00:26:32,400 --> 00:26:33,700
I already figured

481
00:26:34,070 --> 00:26:36,250
you'd record our call

482
00:26:36,350 --> 00:26:38,900
and have Sa Ziyi figure out who I am.

483
00:26:39,680 --> 00:26:40,290
Good.

484
00:26:40,590 --> 00:26:41,940
You're very cautious.

485
00:26:42,310 --> 00:26:43,140
I like that.

486
00:26:43,680 --> 00:26:45,010
Clearly,

487
00:26:45,400 --> 00:26:47,090
you didn't get the answer you wanted

488
00:26:47,110 --> 00:26:48,660
from Sa Ziyi.

489
00:26:51,880 --> 00:26:52,860
How is she now?

490
00:26:57,000 --> 00:26:57,700
Du Li.

491
00:26:58,070 --> 00:26:59,860
How is Sa Ziyi now?

492
00:27:00,240 --> 00:27:01,290
She's asleep.

493
00:27:01,400 --> 00:27:02,250
And she's not waking up.

494
00:27:02,960 --> 00:27:03,660
Good.

495
00:27:06,310 --> 00:27:07,330
So what now?

496
00:27:07,790 --> 00:27:08,530
What do we do?

497
00:27:09,240 --> 00:27:10,090
Nothing.

498
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:12,700
Now we wait for Customs
to make its move.

499
00:27:13,920 --> 00:27:15,940
You can save this number now.

500
00:27:16,310 --> 00:27:17,220
Wait for my call.

501
00:27:50,040 --> 00:27:54,040
[Five Years Later
2024]

502
00:28:43,110 --> 00:28:44,050
Mom, I'm off.

503
00:29:48,270 --> 00:29:49,380
This is outrageous.

504
00:29:50,440 --> 00:29:52,250
They actually planted a doll
in your house.

505
00:29:52,680 --> 00:29:53,380
Cong,

506
00:29:54,200 --> 00:29:55,730
you need to protect yourself
and your family.

507
00:29:56,480 --> 00:29:57,380
Do you want Customs to arrange

508
00:29:57,550 --> 00:29:58,900
a temporary place for you to stay?

509
00:29:59,720 --> 00:30:00,380
No need.

510
00:30:01,750 --> 00:30:03,090
I thought about it on my way here.

511
00:30:03,480 --> 00:30:04,700
Whoever left that doll

512
00:30:05,000 --> 00:30:06,050
probably meant no harm.

513
00:30:06,270 --> 00:30:07,090
Otherwise,

514
00:30:07,110 --> 00:30:08,220
they would've made a move.

515
00:30:09,400 --> 00:30:11,290
I think they left it

516
00:30:11,310 --> 00:30:12,380
to warn me.

517
00:30:13,160 --> 00:30:13,770
Warn you?

518
00:30:16,350 --> 00:30:17,530
Other people might not get it,

519
00:30:17,680 --> 00:30:18,490
but

520
00:30:18,880 --> 00:30:19,660
I do.

521
00:30:22,750 --> 00:30:23,330
Look.

522
00:30:24,070 --> 00:30:25,420
The way the scarf

523
00:30:25,720 --> 00:30:26,900
is tied on the doll

524
00:30:27,270 --> 00:30:29,250
looks just like a flight attendant's.

525
00:30:29,510 --> 00:30:30,140
And

526
00:30:30,270 --> 00:30:31,380
there's a heart on its chest.

527
00:30:32,160 --> 00:30:32,980
It probably

528
00:30:33,200 --> 00:30:34,570
points to Shen Taotao.

529
00:30:34,590 --> 00:30:35,420
Shen Taotao?

530
00:30:36,510 --> 00:30:37,290
A flight attendant.

531
00:30:37,960 --> 00:30:39,050
She was arrested a few days ago

532
00:30:39,200 --> 00:30:41,180
for illegally bringing ivory jewelry

533
00:30:41,400 --> 00:30:42,220
into the country.

534
00:30:42,550 --> 00:30:43,980
The relationship between you two is…

535
00:30:44,480 --> 00:30:45,250
She likes me.

536
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:46,770
Lately,

537
00:30:47,070 --> 00:30:48,090
she's gotten close to my mom.

538
00:30:50,830 --> 00:30:51,620
So she's after you.

539
00:30:52,830 --> 00:30:54,530
How many people know about this?

540
00:30:55,000 --> 00:30:56,420
She's pretty bold about it.

541
00:30:56,480 --> 00:30:57,570
Quite a few people know.

542
00:31:00,550 --> 00:31:01,570
So this doll means…

543
00:31:02,160 --> 00:31:03,530
It's probably hinting

544
00:31:03,550 --> 00:31:05,180
that I should keep following

545
00:31:05,200 --> 00:31:06,250
the Shen Taotao lead.

546
00:31:08,640 --> 00:31:09,290
Mr. Shen.

547
00:31:09,960 --> 00:31:10,700
I think this doll

548
00:31:10,720 --> 00:31:12,770
isn't quite like the others.

549
00:31:13,110 --> 00:31:14,460
But whether it's connected

550
00:31:14,480 --> 00:31:15,490
to the doll from three years ago,

551
00:31:15,510 --> 00:31:16,460
we don't know yet.

552
00:31:16,640 --> 00:31:17,940
But one thing is certain:

553
00:31:18,110 --> 00:31:19,290
Long Shuo didn't place it.

554
00:31:19,720 --> 00:31:20,980
Because whoever left it

555
00:31:21,440 --> 00:31:22,090
clearly

556
00:31:22,350 --> 00:31:23,530
didn't want many people to know.

557
00:31:24,920 --> 00:31:26,730
Based on everything

558
00:31:26,920 --> 00:31:27,730
that's happened lately,

559
00:31:27,960 --> 00:31:28,810
I have a theory.

560
00:31:29,590 --> 00:31:30,140
First,

561
00:31:30,440 --> 00:31:32,140
Shen Taotao knows I'm with Customs.

562
00:31:32,640 --> 00:31:34,730
She probably wouldn't get involved
in smuggling

563
00:31:34,960 --> 00:31:36,530
unless someone forced her to.

564
00:31:37,960 --> 00:31:38,620
Second,

565
00:31:39,200 --> 00:31:40,250
Long Shuo's appearance

566
00:31:40,400 --> 00:31:41,460
may have forced the ring

567
00:31:41,830 --> 00:31:43,420
to cut off one part to save the rest.

568
00:31:43,960 --> 00:31:44,810
They were hit hard.

569
00:31:45,310 --> 00:31:46,380
Is it possible

570
00:31:46,880 --> 00:31:48,290
that Shen Taotao and Ken

571
00:31:48,400 --> 00:31:49,460
were both set up to take the fall?

572
00:31:50,240 --> 00:31:51,380
So you mean

573
00:31:52,030 --> 00:31:55,090
they were both pawns
from different factions within the ring?

574
00:31:55,960 --> 00:31:57,140
If that's true,

575
00:31:57,160 --> 00:31:58,810
then it means

576
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:00,010
the ring has already split.

577
00:32:03,200 --> 00:32:04,180
You took the long way around,

578
00:32:04,200 --> 00:32:05,420
but now I get it.

579
00:32:05,880 --> 00:32:06,860
This doll

580
00:32:07,200 --> 00:32:08,460
was probably planted by one side.

581
00:32:09,240 --> 00:32:10,420
Whoever left it

582
00:32:10,880 --> 00:32:12,770
wanted to keep it quiet.

583
00:32:13,110 --> 00:32:13,900
And you

584
00:32:14,830 --> 00:32:16,330
want to make a big splash

585
00:32:16,550 --> 00:32:17,770
and see what happens.

586
00:32:18,440 --> 00:32:18,900
Yes.

587
00:32:21,510 --> 00:32:21,980
All right.

588
00:32:23,440 --> 00:32:24,530
I'll take care of it.

589
00:32:42,830 --> 00:32:43,620
Zhang.

590
00:32:45,070 --> 00:32:45,730
Mr. Xiang.

591
00:32:46,440 --> 00:32:47,810
Come on in.

592
00:32:48,270 --> 00:32:49,530
I'm up on the second floor.

593
00:32:49,550 --> 00:32:50,770
Just come up these stairs.

594
00:32:50,790 --> 00:32:51,220
Okay.

595
00:33:04,440 --> 00:33:05,290
Easy there.

596
00:33:20,000 --> 00:33:20,860
That step's steep.

597
00:33:20,880 --> 00:33:21,380
Watch your step.

598
00:33:21,400 --> 00:33:21,900
Okay.

599
00:33:22,160 --> 00:33:22,940
It looked nice here,

600
00:33:22,960 --> 00:33:24,420
so I snapped a couple shots.

601
00:33:25,680 --> 00:33:26,700
- Come on. - Okay.

602
00:33:27,750 --> 00:33:29,140
It's the weekend.
Why aren't you taking a break?

603
00:33:29,160 --> 00:33:30,140
What brings you here?

604
00:33:30,160 --> 00:33:31,700
See? I came prepared.

605
00:33:32,270 --> 00:33:33,380
They all say you're great with a camera,

606
00:33:33,400 --> 00:33:35,420
so I thought I'd come learn from you.

607
00:33:35,680 --> 00:33:37,010
You all want to learn from me.

608
00:33:37,400 --> 00:33:38,900
What's with you people?

609
00:33:40,070 --> 00:33:41,220
Come on, have a seat.

610
00:33:45,070 --> 00:33:46,250
Do you usually drink tea?

611
00:33:47,550 --> 00:33:48,660
Not really.

612
00:33:48,880 --> 00:33:50,290
Then it'll be easy to fool you.

613
00:33:50,750 --> 00:33:51,570
Go right ahead.

614
00:33:53,110 --> 00:33:54,290
This is all old-tree tea.

615
00:33:54,350 --> 00:33:55,490
I just brewed some.

616
00:33:55,590 --> 00:33:56,380
Give it a try.

617
00:33:56,960 --> 00:33:57,570
Okay.

618
00:34:08,280 --> 00:34:09,090
Mr. Xiang,

619
00:34:09,670 --> 00:34:11,420
this place is really something.

620
00:34:12,550 --> 00:34:13,860
Everything here is old.

621
00:34:14,150 --> 00:34:15,090
Very rustic.

622
00:34:16,280 --> 00:34:17,380
Old things are good.

623
00:34:17,670 --> 00:34:18,490
They've got character.

624
00:34:19,630 --> 00:34:20,780
Not many young people

625
00:34:20,800 --> 00:34:22,300
like old things.

626
00:34:26,480 --> 00:34:27,460
Is this Mr. Guo?

627
00:34:28,800 --> 00:34:29,780
Right after graduation.

628
00:34:31,840 --> 00:34:33,690
Then… who are the other two?

629
00:34:35,880 --> 00:34:36,420
Well,

630
00:34:37,670 --> 00:34:38,780
this is Guo Shuliang,

631
00:34:38,960 --> 00:34:39,820
Guo Cong's father.

632
00:34:41,030 --> 00:34:43,210
This was taken
when we first started the company.

633
00:34:43,760 --> 00:34:44,650
That was 20 years ago.

634
00:34:49,800 --> 00:34:51,740
This chair's an old piece, too.

635
00:34:52,320 --> 00:34:53,050
It's really heavy.

636
00:34:53,070 --> 00:34:54,340
Yeah, it is.

637
00:34:56,480 --> 00:34:58,490
You must be pretty nostalgic.

638
00:34:58,590 --> 00:34:59,530
It's been 20 years,

639
00:34:59,960 --> 00:35:02,820
and this place hardly seems
to have changed.

640
00:35:02,960 --> 00:35:04,170
Right, not much.

641
00:35:04,920 --> 00:35:06,650
Other than a few small repairs,

642
00:35:06,670 --> 00:35:07,940
I barely touched a thing.

643
00:35:09,150 --> 00:35:10,130
Around here,

644
00:35:10,230 --> 00:35:11,690
we work with old furniture.

645
00:35:11,840 --> 00:35:12,740
If you make it look too new,

646
00:35:12,760 --> 00:35:13,420
it just feels wrong.

647
00:35:15,030 --> 00:35:15,690
Here, have some tea.

648
00:35:15,710 --> 00:35:16,210
Thanks.

649
00:35:16,840 --> 00:35:18,050
After tea, I'll show you around.

650
00:35:18,400 --> 00:35:18,940
Sounds good.

651
00:35:26,710 --> 00:35:27,780
Come on, Zhang.

652
00:35:28,920 --> 00:35:30,740
Come take a look at my darkroom.

653
00:35:39,230 --> 00:35:40,130
This is where I usually

654
00:35:40,710 --> 00:35:42,260
develop my film.

655
00:35:43,280 --> 00:35:44,860
I do it all myself.

656
00:35:45,840 --> 00:35:46,940
This is where

657
00:35:47,400 --> 00:35:50,380
I do the whole film-developing process.

658
00:35:53,230 --> 00:35:54,690
If you want a bigger print,

659
00:35:54,710 --> 00:35:55,570
you've got to move

660
00:35:55,960 --> 00:35:57,530
this machine up.

661
00:35:57,880 --> 00:35:59,380
Once the image comes through here,

662
00:35:59,440 --> 00:36:00,490
you take the photo paper over here

663
00:36:00,510 --> 00:36:01,780
and do the same thing.

664
00:36:01,840 --> 00:36:02,530
Then back again?

665
00:36:02,550 --> 00:36:03,130
Right.

666
00:36:03,440 --> 00:36:04,860
I'll teach you when we get the chance.

667
00:36:04,880 --> 00:36:05,780
- Is that okay? - Sure.

668
00:36:11,920 --> 00:36:13,090
Careful. Don't get cut.

669
00:36:13,480 --> 00:36:13,980
I'm good…

670
00:36:20,230 --> 00:36:21,570
Is this Shen Taotao?

671
00:36:23,110 --> 00:36:23,610
This…

672
00:36:24,150 --> 00:36:24,980
How did…

673
00:36:26,710 --> 00:36:29,010
I was going to give her this photo.

674
00:36:29,800 --> 00:36:31,690
But I had no idea
she was that kind of person.

675
00:36:31,800 --> 00:36:33,490
So I smashed it in a fit of anger.

676
00:36:35,920 --> 00:36:38,740
Did you really like Shen Taotao?

677
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:40,420
I wouldn't say that.

678
00:36:40,710 --> 00:36:41,820
I just thought

679
00:36:42,360 --> 00:36:44,340
she was really good to Cong.

680
00:36:44,710 --> 00:36:47,130
So I figured
maybe I could help things along.

681
00:36:47,150 --> 00:36:48,260
Maybe they'd be a good match.

682
00:36:48,760 --> 00:36:49,820
What about me and him?

683
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:56,170
I like Guo Cong, too.

684
00:36:57,030 --> 00:36:57,940
Do you think

685
00:36:58,360 --> 00:36:59,460
we'd be a good match?

686
00:37:08,360 --> 00:37:10,690
Then why are you telling me this?

687
00:37:13,440 --> 00:37:16,530
Because he listens to you
more than anyone.

688
00:37:18,190 --> 00:37:20,010
And I don't want you

689
00:37:20,030 --> 00:37:21,380
setting him up with anyone else.

690
00:37:23,360 --> 00:37:23,980
I see.

691
00:37:25,320 --> 00:37:26,650
So this whole photography thing

692
00:37:26,670 --> 00:37:28,090
was just a cover.

693
00:37:28,190 --> 00:37:29,170
What you really want

694
00:37:29,190 --> 00:37:31,010
is my help with this.

695
00:37:34,880 --> 00:37:36,170
I really do want

696
00:37:36,630 --> 00:37:37,980
to learn more

697
00:37:38,320 --> 00:37:39,650
about Guo Cong from you.

698
00:37:40,150 --> 00:37:41,460
What do you want to know about him?

699
00:37:42,510 --> 00:37:43,690
Well,

700
00:37:44,400 --> 00:37:45,010
everything!

701
00:37:47,630 --> 00:37:48,170
All right.

702
00:37:48,190 --> 00:37:49,340
Everything about Cong.

703
00:37:51,480 --> 00:37:53,490
Then I'll have to tell you
about him properly,

704
00:37:53,960 --> 00:37:55,050
nice and slow.

705
00:37:58,480 --> 00:37:59,650
I'm all ears.

706
00:38:08,000 --> 00:38:09,690
Mr. Guo has been in there
for almost an hour.

707
00:38:09,710 --> 00:38:10,940
Why isn't he back yet?

708
00:38:11,280 --> 00:38:14,170
And Shen Taotao
specifically asked to see him.

709
00:38:14,190 --> 00:38:15,420
What could she possibly have to say?

710
00:38:16,880 --> 00:38:17,650
No idea.

711
00:38:18,280 --> 00:38:20,090
Shen Taotao likes Mr. Guo.

712
00:38:20,440 --> 00:38:22,170
When she's around Mr. Guo,

713
00:38:22,190 --> 00:38:24,530
she tends to rely on him
almost like family.

714
00:38:24,710 --> 00:38:25,940
That's actually a good thing.

715
00:38:25,960 --> 00:38:27,340
So when she's with Mr. Guo,

716
00:38:27,360 --> 00:38:30,130
she can let her guard down, open up,

717
00:38:30,190 --> 00:38:31,980
and say what's on her mind.

718
00:38:32,960 --> 00:38:33,570
No wonder

719
00:38:33,590 --> 00:38:36,420
so many suspects in the past

720
00:38:36,480 --> 00:38:38,740
turned themselves in
after their families talked to them.

721
00:38:39,550 --> 00:38:40,300
That also explains

722
00:38:40,320 --> 00:38:42,740
why the anti-smuggling unit agreed
to let her see Mr. Guo.

723
00:38:43,360 --> 00:38:44,210
Now I get it.

724
00:38:44,480 --> 00:38:46,130
Maybe Mr. Guo
really can get her to talk.

725
00:38:48,030 --> 00:38:49,740
- Mentor, how's it go? - Mr. Guo.

726
00:38:51,510 --> 00:38:52,530
Did Shen Taotao talk?

727
00:38:52,630 --> 00:38:53,380
She did.

728
00:38:59,000 --> 00:38:59,780
Before, she said

729
00:38:59,800 --> 00:39:02,050
she was bringing in goods on her own
and selling them online.

730
00:39:02,590 --> 00:39:04,170
But now she's admitted

731
00:39:04,440 --> 00:39:05,860
that was only a small part of it.

732
00:39:06,190 --> 00:39:07,610
Most of her goods

733
00:39:07,710 --> 00:39:09,530
were sold to a woman named Liu Yang.

734
00:39:10,800 --> 00:39:12,860
She met Liu Yang two years ago.

735
00:39:12,960 --> 00:39:13,780
Liu Yang

736
00:39:13,880 --> 00:39:15,690
offered her a huge cut

737
00:39:16,360 --> 00:39:17,940
to get her to move goods for her.

738
00:39:19,550 --> 00:39:20,900
According to the anti-smuggling unit,

739
00:39:21,030 --> 00:39:23,010
Liu Yang is a frequent traveler,

740
00:39:23,230 --> 00:39:25,420
making at least
one cross-border trip a week.

741
00:39:25,630 --> 00:39:26,420
But when they checked her luggage,

742
00:39:26,440 --> 00:39:27,860
they didn't find any contraband.

743
00:39:29,230 --> 00:39:30,300
There's more.

744
00:39:30,360 --> 00:39:31,090
Liu Yang

745
00:39:31,110 --> 00:39:32,210
owns an MCN agency

746
00:39:32,320 --> 00:39:33,380
with a lot of streamers.

747
00:39:34,110 --> 00:39:35,940
They sell high-end luxury goods

748
00:39:36,070 --> 00:39:37,340
in large quantities,

749
00:39:37,440 --> 00:39:38,210
but

750
00:39:38,440 --> 00:39:39,210
the source is unclear.

751
00:39:39,630 --> 00:39:40,860
The decision from Customs is

752
00:39:40,920 --> 00:39:42,090
not to spook them yet.

753
00:39:42,480 --> 00:39:44,380
First, we figure out Liu Yang's
smuggling network,

754
00:39:44,550 --> 00:39:45,490
then we reel them in.

755
00:39:46,510 --> 00:39:49,340
Shen Taotao's given us
a lot more to work with now.

756
00:39:49,590 --> 00:39:51,300
Wouldn't that make the amount involved
even bigger?

757
00:39:51,510 --> 00:39:53,170
If the information she gave us

758
00:39:53,190 --> 00:39:54,050
helps us

759
00:39:54,070 --> 00:39:55,980
catch Liu Yang and her ring,

760
00:39:56,110 --> 00:39:57,210
that'll count in her favor.

761
00:40:09,800 --> 00:40:10,920
[Liu Yang Profile]

762
00:40:10,920 --> 00:40:11,420
[Liu Yang Profile]
Liu Yang.

763
00:40:11,440 --> 00:40:12,380
[Liu Yang Profile]
Female, 35.

764
00:40:12,400 --> 00:40:13,300
[Liu Yang Profile]
A Binhai local.

765
00:40:13,360 --> 00:40:15,050
[Liu Yang Profile]
She used to run restaurants in Binhai.

766
00:40:15,110 --> 00:40:16,210
Two years ago, she opened
a Chinese restaurant

767
00:40:16,230 --> 00:40:17,260
in Seoul, South Korea.

768
00:40:17,760 --> 00:40:19,090
After that, she started traveling
back and forth

769
00:40:19,110 --> 00:40:20,170
between Binhai and Seoul.

770
00:40:20,960 --> 00:40:21,900
That's around the same time

771
00:40:21,960 --> 00:40:22,860
when she got Shen Taotao

772
00:40:22,880 --> 00:40:23,980
to move goods for her.

773
00:40:24,400 --> 00:40:25,210
In the past two months,

774
00:40:25,230 --> 00:40:26,090
her cross-border trips

775
00:40:26,110 --> 00:40:27,860
have increased to once or twice a week,

776
00:40:28,030 --> 00:40:29,260
usually same-day round trips.

777
00:40:29,960 --> 00:40:32,420
By regulation,
travelers making frequent short trips

778
00:40:32,440 --> 00:40:34,050
may carry only travel essentials.

779
00:40:34,480 --> 00:40:36,420
If she were carrying
high-end luxury goods,

780
00:40:36,440 --> 00:40:37,610
we definitely would've found them.

781
00:40:38,230 --> 00:40:39,650
That's the strange part.

782
00:40:39,710 --> 00:40:41,300
Every time she enters,
she's completely clean.

783
00:40:41,320 --> 00:40:42,530
No contraband at all.

784
00:40:42,880 --> 00:40:45,380
And even if she had to manage
her Seoul branch,

785
00:40:45,440 --> 00:40:47,300
there's no reason to fly that often.

786
00:40:47,590 --> 00:40:48,490
Something's definitely off.

787
00:40:48,920 --> 00:40:49,900
Zhang Yu is right.

788
00:40:50,480 --> 00:40:52,380
According to the airline's
ticketing records,

789
00:40:52,480 --> 00:40:54,490
Liu Yang will be entering
this afternoon.

790
00:40:54,760 --> 00:40:55,460
Stay sharp.

791
00:40:57,190 --> 00:40:57,940
Wrap it up.

792
00:40:57,960 --> 00:40:58,690
Get ready to rotate.

793
00:41:10,440 --> 00:41:11,170
Zhang Yu.

794
00:41:11,840 --> 00:41:12,820
Come out here a second.

795
00:41:22,190 --> 00:41:23,010
What's up, Mentor?

796
00:41:23,670 --> 00:41:25,460
What are you and Uncle Xiang up to?

797
00:41:26,840 --> 00:41:28,380
I'm learning photography

798
00:41:28,440 --> 00:41:29,340
from Mr. Xiang.

799
00:41:30,840 --> 00:41:31,460
Then why does he

800
00:41:31,480 --> 00:41:33,050
keep bringing you up
to my mom every day?

801
00:41:34,150 --> 00:41:36,940
Maybe it's because

802
00:41:36,960 --> 00:41:39,780
I'm really good at being a trainee.

803
00:41:43,480 --> 00:41:46,170
Whatever you two are up to,

804
00:41:46,800 --> 00:41:48,050
you report it to me. Got it?

805
00:41:48,360 --> 00:41:49,380
Come on, Mentor.

806
00:41:49,480 --> 00:41:49,860
I mean,

807
00:41:50,070 --> 00:41:52,690
do I have to report things
outside of work, too?

808
00:41:58,030 --> 00:41:58,610
Here's the thing.

809
00:41:58,920 --> 00:42:00,050
My uncle wanted me to ask

810
00:42:00,150 --> 00:42:01,570
when you're free
to come over for dinner.

811
00:42:03,000 --> 00:42:03,860
Dinner at your place?

812
00:42:05,510 --> 00:42:06,460
I'm free anytime.

813
00:42:07,880 --> 00:42:09,650
Then come over tomorrow.

814
00:42:11,110 --> 00:42:11,530
Okay.

815
00:42:13,000 --> 00:42:13,860
Then I'm heading back on duty.

816
00:42:30,510 --> 00:42:31,980
I just got to China Customs.

817
00:42:34,320 --> 00:42:36,010
I took the first flight over
this morning.

818
00:42:39,190 --> 00:42:40,010
Okay.

819
00:42:40,230 --> 00:42:41,380
Let's have dinner tonight.

820
00:42:42,230 --> 00:42:42,940
Wait for me.

821
00:42:47,320 --> 00:42:48,420
Hello. China Customs.

822
00:42:48,440 --> 00:42:48,980
This way, please.

823
00:42:49,920 --> 00:42:50,420
Thank you.

824
00:42:52,800 --> 00:42:53,530
Thank you for your cooperation.

825
00:42:55,400 --> 00:42:55,980
Attention, all units.

826
00:42:56,000 --> 00:42:56,940
Attention, all units.

827
00:42:57,110 --> 00:42:58,340
Liu Yang just passed
the diversion checkpoint.

828
00:43:30,800 --> 00:43:37,360
♪There's a place of simple,
everyday warmth♪

829
00:43:38,280 --> 00:43:45,000
♪A door left open
for the wandering soul♪

830
00:43:45,920 --> 00:43:52,440
♪A humble table still warm with love♪

831
00:43:52,680 --> 00:43:56,320
♪After you've tasted every high and low♪

832
00:43:56,600 --> 00:44:00,240
♪Come home, I'll keep you warm♪

833
00:44:01,000 --> 00:44:07,680
♪Where the days begin and end♪

834
00:44:08,440 --> 00:44:15,320
♪A light still on for the ones
who've lost their way♪

835
00:44:16,120 --> 00:44:22,680
♪An embrace waiting just for you♪

836
00:44:22,960 --> 00:44:26,680
♪Through every passing season♪

837
00:44:26,800 --> 00:44:30,480
♪Even if you return with nothing at all♪

838
00:44:31,120 --> 00:44:34,600
♪Turn around and look♪

839
00:44:34,800 --> 00:44:38,600
♪That door's still open♪

840
00:44:38,800 --> 00:44:42,440
♪A light still burning♪

841
00:44:42,520 --> 00:44:46,240
♪Waiting there for you♪

842
00:44:46,400 --> 00:44:49,920
♪Turn around and look♪

843
00:44:50,160 --> 00:44:53,960
♪Someone's still waiting♪

844
00:44:54,160 --> 00:44:57,760
♪Watching the dusk settle in♪

845
00:44:57,840 --> 00:45:01,560
♪Waiting for the break of dawn♪

846
00:45:03,320 --> 00:45:07,000
♪It's always there♪
